title: Kendall Jenner, Urban Cowgirl, Brings Western-Inspired Style to the City
text: Kendall Jenner Brings Urban Cowgirl Style to New York Fashion Week February 11, 2017 11:31 PM by Maria Ward Photo: AKM-GSI For a Los Angeles native, Kendall Jenner sure is big fan of fringe. There was the dark-suede Religion jacket the model practically lived in last summer followed by the shredded leather micro-mini skirt she wore just last night in New York City. And while earlier today in SoHo Jenner’s look bore no evidence of fringe—aside from the frayed hem on her two-tone cropped jeans—it seemed clear that stylistically, Jenner is looking westward. Her python stiletto booties served as a citified take onthe cowboy boot, with a pointed toe and grommet studs in place of spurs, while her chocolate-brown leather overcoat with inline shearling recalled the bomber jackets of Urban Cowboy. Futuristic sunglasses, on the other hand, came with a modern finish, while a Louis Vuitton Paris monogrammed tee positioned the look for a chic new frontier. Paris Fashion Week, perhaps?
